        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "A vector field is a (smooth) section of the tangent bundle: `ContMDiffSection I E n (TangentSpace I)`, or unbundled `Π x : M, TangentSpace I x`. The cotangent bundle exists only implicitly as `Π x : M, TangentSpace I x →L[𝕜] 𝕜` (see `extDerivFun`); there is no named `CotangentBundle`/dual-bundle declaration.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent_bundle?oldid=1351233929",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "is a vector field on",
          "prefix": "e vector spaces ). A section of ",
