          "value": "definition"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Mathlib has no `Parallelizable` predicate and no theorem relating it to triviality of the tangent bundle. The closest infrastructure is local frames (`IsLocalFrameOn`, Mathlib.Geometry.Manifold.VectorBundle.LocalFrame) and the trivial bundle `Bundle.Trivial`, but no global-frame / parallelizability notion.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent_bundle?oldid=1351233929",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "is parallelizable if and only if the tangent bundle is trivial",
          "prefix": " of . By definition, a manifold ",
          "suffix": " . By definition, a manifold is "
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "urn:wikilean:Tangent_bundle:anno-5",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": "classifying",
