        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Not formalized. Mathlib defines spheres as manifolds (`Mathlib.Geometry.Manifold.Instances.Sphere`) but neither parallelizability of S^1/S^3/S^7 nor framings of S^n are present; the underlying parallelizability/framing notions do not exist.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent_bundle?oldid=1351233929",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "sphere S n is framed for all n , but parallelizable only for",
          "prefix": "For example, the n -dimensional ",
          "suffix": " n = 1, 3, 7 (by results of Bott"
        }
      }
    },
