        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "`tangentMap I I' f : TangentBundle I M → TangentBundle I' M'` is the bundled derivative; `ContMDiff.contMDiff_tangentMap` shows that if `f` is `C^n` then `tangentMap f` is `C^m` for `m + 1 ≤ n` (and `ContMDiff.continuous_tangentMap` for continuity).",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent_bundle?oldid=1351233929",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "its derivative is a smooth function",
          "prefix": "ion, with and smooth manifolds, ",
          "suffix": " . The tangent bundle comes equi"
