          "value": "definition"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "`tangentBundleCore I M : VectorBundleCore 𝕜 M E (atlas H M)` builds the topology and (for `C^{n+1}` `M`) the `C^n` vector-bundle/manifold structure on `TangentBundle I M` via the chart-indexed coordinate changes (Jacobians `fderivWithin` of `extend`-coordinate changes); the topology instance and `TangentBundle.chartAt` come from this.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent_bundle?oldid=1351233929",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "We use these maps to define the topology and smooth structure on",
          "prefix": " all . We may then define a map ",
          "suffix": " . A subset of is open if and on"
        }
