        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "For the model space `H` (e.g. `E = R^n` with `I = 𝓘(𝕜, E)`), `tangentBundleModelSpaceHomeomorph : TangentBundle I H ≃ₜ ModelProd H E` exhibits the tangent bundle as homeomorphic to the product, and the trivialization is the identity (`trivializationAt_model_space_apply`). This is the model-space triviality rather than a general 'TM of R^n is trivial' statement.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent_bundle?oldid=1351233929",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "In this case the tangent bundle is trivial",
          "prefix": "e simplest example is that of . ",
          "suffix": ": each is canonically isomorphic"
        }
      }
    },
