        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "tagging",
          "value": "definition"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "`ContMDiffSection` is exactly a section `s : Π x, V x` (with `s.toFun` satisfying `proj ∘ s = id`) that is `C^n`; applied to `V = TangentSpace I` it is a vector field. Continuity of the projection makes the section condition `π ∘ s = id`.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent_bundle?oldid=1351233929",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "such a map is called a section",
          "prefix": " the language of fiber bundles, ",
          "suffix": " . A vector field on is therefor"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "urn:wikilean:Tangent_bundle:anno-21",
